<h1 id="toc0"><span>Usage</span></h1>
<p>On any wiki:</p>
<div class="code">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;:scp-wiki:theme:black-highlighter-theme]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;:scp-wiki:component:collapsible-sidebar]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;:scp-wiki:theme:memoria]]</span></p>
</div>
<p>For the white-ish text box that you'll need to see the text over the background gradient:</p>
<div class="code">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;textbox&quot;]]</span><br />
Text/code whatever will go in here, as normal.<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/div]]</span></p>
</div>
<p>For the Solomonari &quot;scripture&quot;:</p>
<div class="code">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;type1&quot;]]</span><br />
You'll need to use the &quot;@@ @@&quot; symbols to separate paragraphs and<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[&gt;]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[span&#32;style=&quot;font-family:var(--body-font);&#32;font-size:&#32;calc(var(--base-font-size)&#32;*&#32;1.00);&#32;color:&#32;#000000;&quot;]]-&#32;//This&#32;is&#32;the&#32;&quot;attribution&quot;//[[/span]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/&gt;]]</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[/div]]</span></p>
</div>
<div class="type1">
<p><sup>7</sup>And it came to pass that in those days there went forth throughout the land, a call to explain what the scripture looked like. <sup>8</sup>It was then that the Prophet stood forth and spake with the words of a crafter, <sup>9</sup>&quot;Lo, at this very hour I say unto thee, look unto my words and see what purpose these words has revealed to thee.&quot;<br /></p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><span style="font-family:var(--body-font); font-size: calc(var(--base-font-size) * 1.00); color: #000000;">- <em>The Book of Attribution, 1:7-9; The Solomonari Valkzaron</em></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id="toc1"><span>What this is:</span></h1>
<blockquote>
<p>This theme was developed by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/malycegraves" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4916887); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4916887&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606640171" alt="MalyceGraves" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4916887)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/malycegraves" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4916887); return false;">MalyceGraves</a></span> to be used in conjunction with tales and SCP articles written in and for the Canon <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/memoria-adytum">In Memoria, Adytum</a>.</p>
<p>This theme is licensed under CC BY-SA 3.0</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 id="toc2"><span>Additionally</span></h2>
<p>This is a Black Highlighter + BHL Collapsible Sidebar based theme. You will need to import the Black Highlighter theme as well in order to use this theme. <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/theme:black-highlighter">To learn more go here.</a></p>
